01:20:26,197 --> 01:20:28,240
I hope you find what
you're looking for.

1251
01:20:29,033 --> 01:20:29,951
Good luck.

1252
01:20:43,131 --> 01:20:48,386
<i>Everybody talks about
a new world in the morning</i>

1253
01:20:49,011 --> 01:20:53,766
<i>A new world in the morning
so they say</i>

1254
01:20:54,809 --> 01:21:00,064
<i>I myself don't talk about
a new world in the morning</i>

1255
01:21:00,523 --> 01:21:04,694
<i>A new world in the morning
that's today</i>

1256
01:21:05,403 --> 01:21:10,449
<i>And I can feel
a new tomorrow coming on</i>

1257
01:21:10,908 --> 01:21:17,122
<i>And I don't know why
I have to make a song</i>

1258
01:21:17,957 --> 01:21:23,003
<i>Everybody talks about
a new world in the morning</i>

1259
01:21:23,671 --> 01:21:27,966
<i>New world in the morning
takes so long</i>

1260
01:21:35,265 --> 01:21:36,309
Father?

1261
01:21:36,810 --> 01:21:38,185
Hello.

1262
01:21:41,355 --> 01:21:43,024
You are going to Dublin?

1263
01:21:45,318 --> 01:21:46,653
Yeah.

1264
01:21:48,529 --> 01:21:50,948
Just getting away
for a while, you know.

1265
01:21:52,826 --> 01:21:56,037
I heard about your church.
A terrible thing.

1266
01:21:57,538 --> 01:21:58,539
Yes.

1267
01:21:59,373 --> 01:22:01,626
You must be very upset.

1268
01:22:06,506 --> 01:22:08,298
Yes, I am.

1269
01:22:15,640 --> 01:22:19,685
I'm bringing him home...
to his family in Italy.

1270
01:22:22,229 --> 01:22:24,858
Dublin and then... Rome.

1271
01:22:27,484 --> 01:22:28,944
How have you been?

1272
01:22:29,028 --> 01:22:31,780
People here have
been very kind to me.

1273
01:22:31,864 --> 01:22:34,283
No, I mean...

1274
01:22:38,496 --> 01:22:39,831
You know...

1275
01:22:40,957 --> 01:22:43,208
sometimes I think
I cannot go on.

1276
01:22:45,002 --> 01:22:46,378
But...

1277
01:22:48,172 --> 01:22:49,882
...I will go on.

1278
01:25:20,574 --> 01:25:22,034
Father.

1279
01:25:22,493 --> 01:25:24,162
Little early for Mass.

1280
01:25:24,537 --> 01:25:27,832
Doctor Harte was out fishing
at the crack of dawn.

1281
01:25:27,914 --> 01:25:30,417
He begrudgingly
gave me a ride.

1282
01:25:30,710 --> 01:25:32,462
Where are you headed?

1283
01:25:33,671 --> 01:25:35,047
Just down the beach.

1284
01:25:35,213 --> 01:25:36,632
Can I come along?

1285
01:25:36,841 --> 01:25:39,469
Not really, no.
Maybe later.

1286
01:25:40,261 --> 01:25:43,389
That's fine. You know,
I don't wanna keep you.

1287
01:25:43,890 --> 01:25:45,891
Did you finish your book?

1288
01:25:46,016 --> 01:25:48,019
Yes, I did. I don't
know how good it is.

1289
01:25:48,560 --> 01:25:52,105
I'm sure it'll be extraordinary.
You're a very fine writer.

1290
01:25:54,775 --> 01:25:56,778
Thank you, James.

1291
01:26:00,030 --> 01:26:01,323
<i>You know you
changed the subject</i>

1292
01:26:01,448 --> 01:26:02,837
<i>the other day
when we were talking?</i>

1293
01:26:03,368 --> 01:26:04,577
What was the subject?

1294
01:26:04,661 --> 01:26:06,746
You know what the subject was.

1295
01:26:07,079 --> 01:26:09,131
I think you committed
a sin of omission there,

1296
01:26:09,157 --> 01:26:10,341
if truth be told.

1297
01:26:11,167 --> 01:26:13,418
Sure there are worse sins
than sins of omission.

1298
01:26:13,502 --> 01:26:15,921
Well now you'd be the expert
in that department, Father.

1299
01:26:16,756 --> 01:26:19,926
I think there's too much talk about sins,
to be honest...

1300
01:26:20,426 --> 01:26:22,427
...and not enough
talk about virtues.

1301
01:26:23,261 --> 01:26:24,930
You might be right.

1302
01:26:26,765 --> 01:26:28,350
What would be
your number one?

1303
01:26:29,101 --> 01:26:32,063
I think forgiveness has
been highly underrated.

1304
01:26:35,190 --> 01:26:36,900
I forgive you.

1305
01:26:38,860 --> 01:26:40,529
Do you forgive me?

1306
01:26:41,863 --> 01:26:43,198
Always.

1307
01:27:04,470 --> 01:27:06,471
Thinking of
throwing yourself in?

1308
01:27:06,639 --> 01:27:08,640
They say that's
the easy way out.

1309
01:27:09,057 --> 01:27:11,894
Nothing easy about it,
I wouldn't have thought.

1310
01:27:15,814 --> 01:27:17,984
I'm in a bad way, Father.

1311
01:27:20,737 --> 01:27:22,779
No, I'm not putting you on.

1312
01:27:24,239 --> 01:27:26,908
The truth is,
I've been in a bad way for...

1313
01:27:28,327 --> 01:27:29,996
...a long time.

1314
01:27:31,288 --> 01:27:33,623
Not wanting
to do anything.

1315
01:27:34,917 --> 01:27:37,587
Feeling of nothing
being worthwhile.

1316
01:27:39,255 --> 01:27:42,007
A sense of disassociation.

1317
01:27:43,717 --> 01:27:45,344
Detachment.

1318
01:27:45,845 --> 01:27:47,846
I had a wife and kids...

1319
01:27:49,181 --> 01:27:51,184
...they meant nothing to me.

1320
01:27:55,354 --> 01:27:58,190
I have money,
it means nothing to me.

1321
01:28:00,275 --> 01:28:01,944
I have life...

1322
01:28:03,863 --> 01:28:05,823
...it means nothing to me.

1323
01:28:10,953 --> 01:28:12,913
Where do you think
it comes from...

1324
01:28:13,747 --> 01:28:14,916
the sense of detachment?

1325
01:28:19,878 --> 01:28:21,380
From nowhere.

1326
01:28:25,091 --> 01:28:26,551
From nowhere.

1327
01:28:33,309 --> 01:28:35,435
Listen, I've to meet
someone now...

1328
01:28:36,395 --> 01:28:38,396
...but I'll call up
to the house after.

1329
01:28:40,440 --> 01:28:41,775
We'll talk.

1330
01:28:44,862 --> 01:28:47,198
Get you back on track.
Okay?

1331
01:28:53,162 --> 01:28:54,997
- Okay?
- Thank you.

1332
01:28:57,250 --> 01:28:58,583
Thank you, Father.

1333
01:28:59,292 --> 01:29:00,336
Thank you.

1334
01:29:00,461 --> 01:29:01,503
All right?

1335
01:29:04,340 --> 01:29:05,716
Are you all right?
Yeah.

1336
01:30:02,273 --> 01:30:05,484
Take your hands out of your pockets.
Slowly.

1337
01:30:06,444 --> 01:30:07,444
Why?

1338
01:30:07,528 --> 01:30:09,279
I heard you had a gun.

1339
01:30:14,993 --> 01:30:17,954
I have to say I'm surprised. Thought
I'd have to go looking for you.

1340
01:30:18,079 --> 01:30:19,081
Just because I'm here,
doesn't mean

1341
01:30:19,206 --> 01:30:20,207
you have to go
through with it.

1342
01:30:20,291 --> 01:30:21,958
Yes, it does.

1343
01:30:23,252 --> 01:30:26,087
It's one of those
self-fulfilling prophecies.

1344
01:30:27,672 --> 01:30:30,134
Did you ever think it would
come to this, though?

1345
01:30:30,384 --> 01:30:33,762
I was hoping it wouldn't. I thought
you were a friend of mine.

1346
01:30:33,845 --> 01:30:36,097
A friend is just an enemy
you haven't made yet.

1347
01:30:37,475 --> 01:30:40,728
Cheap cynicism.
Not cheap, now, no.

1348
01:30:41,895 --> 01:30:44,564
That's a cynicism
that's been hard won.

1349
01:30:45,274 --> 01:30:47,652
That's a cynicism
that's been earned...

1350
01:30:47,734 --> 01:30:51,613
...after a hell of a lot of
physical and psychological torture.

1351
01:30:52,238 --> 01:30:55,784
I take it back, then. But
it's cynicism nonetheless.

1352
01:30:57,453 --> 01:30:59,204
Maybe that's
the difference between us.

1353
01:30:59,329 --> 01:31:01,082
Oh, that's not
the only difference.

1354
01:31:03,167 --> 01:31:04,585
Any regrets?

1355
01:31:04,835 --> 01:31:08,088
I have, yeah. I never got
to finish <i>Moby Dick.</i>

1356
01:31:08,213 --> 01:31:10,091
The whale kills Ahab.
Is that right?

1357
01:31:10,216 --> 01:31:13,802
Then he destroys the rest of the
ship and the crew along with it.

1358
01:31:14,220 --> 01:31:19,432
All except for Ishmael. He
alone escapes to tell thee.

1359
01:31:23,729 --> 01:31:26,399
The burning of the
church I can understand.

1360
01:31:29,193 --> 01:31:31,194
You didn't have
to kill my dog.

1361
01:31:31,737 --> 01:31:33,572
I didn't kill your dog.
I love dogs.

1362
01:31:33,698 --> 01:31:35,533
Why would I do
a thing like that?

1363
01:31:35,658 --> 01:31:37,158
I found him with his throat cut.

1364
01:31:37,243 --> 01:31:40,203
Why would I fucking
kill a dog?! I didn't...

1365
01:31:40,496 --> 01:31:42,163
That was nothing to do with me.

1366
01:31:43,707 --> 01:31:46,085
I am wholly innocent
of that crime.

1367
01:31:50,422 --> 01:31:53,175
I did give Veronica a bit
of a shove that one time.

1368
01:31:53,259 --> 01:31:56,761
I do admit that
and I'm sorry for it.

1369
01:32:01,559 --> 01:32:03,601
Did it upset you,
the dog?

1370
01:32:04,395 --> 01:32:05,604
Yes, it did.

1371
01:32:05,895 --> 01:32:07,230
Did you cry?

1372
01:32:07,439 --> 01:32:09,024
Yes, I did.

1373
01:32:09,108 --> 01:32:10,775
That's nice.

1374
01:32:13,570 --> 01:32:15,280
When you read what
your fellow priests

1375
01:32:15,405 --> 01:32:17,033
did to all those
poor children...

1376
01:32:17,115 --> 01:32:19,118
...over the years,
did you cry then?

1377
01:32:23,913 --> 01:32:26,292
I asked you a question.
Did you cry then?

1378
01:32:27,626 --> 01:32:28,877
No.

1379
01:32:29,462 --> 01:32:30,587
That's right!

1380
01:32:33,631 --> 01:32:34,632
I suppose...

1381
01:32:34,800 --> 01:32:35,801
What?

1382
01:32:38,804 --> 01:32:40,805
I suppose I felt
detached from it.

1383
01:32:40,930 --> 01:32:43,975
The way you are when you read
something in a newspaper...

1384
01:32:51,649 --> 01:32:53,109
Detach yourself from that!

1385
01:32:57,739 --> 01:32:59,908
We were the lucky ones!

1386
01:33:00,658 --> 01:33:04,537
There's bodies buried back there!
Buried like dogs!

1387
01:33:09,460 --> 01:33:10,836
Don't look at me.

1388
01:33:12,128 --> 01:33:14,547
Turn your face away!
Don't look at me!

1389
01:33:20,261 --> 01:33:21,680
No! Run!
Michael, run!

1390
01:33:21,805 --> 01:33:23,181
I'll get Stanton, Father.

1391
01:33:28,104 --> 01:33:30,396
He reminds me of me.

1392
01:33:35,903 --> 01:33:37,988
It's not too late, Jack.

1393
01:33:39,489 --> 01:33:41,242
Yes, it is.

1394
01:33:43,993 --> 01:33:45,787
Yes, it is.

1395
01:33:47,622 --> 01:33:49,041
Say your prayers, Father.

1396
01:33:52,002 --> 01:33:54,003
I've already said them.
